10#include <stdio.h>
11#include "internal/cryptlib.h"
12#include <openssl/objects.h>
13#include <openssl/asn1t.h>
14#include <openssl/x509.h>
15#include "x509_lcl.h"
16
17/*-
18 * X509_ATTRIBUTE: this has the following form:
19 *
20 * typedef struct x509_attributes_st
21 * {
22 * ASN1_OBJECT *object;
23 * STACK_OF(ASN1_TYPE) *set;
24 * } X509_ATTRIBUTE;
25 *
26 */
27
28ASN1_SEQUENCE(X509_ATTRIBUTE) = {
29 ASN1_SIMPLE(X509_ATTRIBUTE, object, ASN1_OBJECT),
30 ASN1_SET_OF(X509_ATTRIBUTE, set, ASN1_ANY)
31} ASN1_SEQUENCE_END(X509_ATTRIBUTE)
32
33IMPLEMENT_ASN1_FUNCTIONS(X509_ATTRIBUTE)
34IMPLEMENT_ASN1_DUP_FUNCTION(X509_ATTRIBUTE)
35
36X509_ATTRIBUTE *X509_ATTRIBUTE_create(int nid, int atrtype, void *value)
37{
38 X509_ATTRIBUTE *ret = NULL;
39 ASN1_TYPE *val = NULL;
40
41 if ((ret = X509_ATTRIBUTE_new()) == NULL)
42 return NULL;
43 ret->object = OBJ_nid2obj(nid);
44 if ((val = ASN1_TYPE_new()) == NULL)
45 goto err;
46 if (!sk_ASN1_TYPE_push(ret->set, val))
47 goto err;
48
49 ASN1_TYPE_set(val, atrtype, value);
50 return ret;
51 err:
52 X509_ATTRIBUTE_free(ret);
53 ASN1_TYPE_free(val);
54 return NULL;
55}
